comments.body:
Did you think about
```c++
template<class RooArgSet_t>
RooCmdArg Conditional(RooArgSet_t&& pdfSet, ...) {
  return Conditional(std::forward<RooArgSet_t>(pdfSet), ...);
}
  ```
  This way, it could collapse into a single constructor, and it would also take a `RooArgList`. I'm not sure if one template function is better than three overloads, but I wanted to put it up as an alternative.

